flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|concentrated|Your clearest route into flow is focused attention that gives the work depth before it opens out. Ideas, movement, and response matter most when they help that careful work become usable.|You can stay with demanding work long enough for the real point to become clear.|You may keep improving the work privately after it needs movement or response.|Let focus build substance, then bring in one fresh angle, one change of state, or one clear response at the right moment.|Depth works best when it still has somewhere to go.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::concentrated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|Flow is likely to come from the close link between focused attention and idea movement. The work is strongest when depth and originality keep each other practical.|You can produce work that is both considered and fresh.|You may keep moving between focus and ideas after the work needs recovery or response.|Use focus and ideas together, then bring in rhythm or conversation before the loop gets too private.|Let the idea move, but keep the work clear.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|graduated|This pattern works as an ordered route: focus first, ideas next, physical rhythm for recovery, and social exchange to check the result. The full sequence matters because each signal gives the work a different kind of range.|You can move from careful thought into original work without losing steadiness.|You may wait too long before the work meets another person or a practical change of state.|Follow the order, but do not wait until the work is finished before using rhythm or response.|Start deep, then widen before the work closes in.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::graduated
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|balanced|Read this result as a flexible flow profile with focus slightly first. Different tasks may need quiet thought, a fresh angle, movement, or conversation, and the value is knowing which condition the work needs now.|You can move between several routes without losing the value of depth.|You may switch routes before one condition has had enough time to help.|Start with the condition that fits the task, then add the signal the work is missing.|Your flow is strongest when the next condition is chosen, not automatic.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::balanced
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm|concentrated|Your clearest route into flow is focused thought that becomes more original and then easier to explain. Physical rhythm is the range to add when the process becomes too mental.|You can build a strong idea before asking it to make sense to someone else.|You may stay with thinking, ideas, and response after your state needs to change.|Use depth to form the work, then add movement or a change of setting before another round of thinking or talk.|Good thinking also needs a change of state.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange_physical_rhythm::concentrated
